Title: Timeline of COVID- 19 in tamil
Description:
COVID -19 🦠நோயை பற்றிய புரிதலை இந்த ஒலிப்பதிவில் 🔊நீங்கள் கேட்டு அறிந்து கொள்ளலாம்.

COVID -19 🦠 நோய் தொற்று எவ்வாறு உடலில் பாதிப்பினை உண்டாக்குகிறது, அதன் விளைவுகளால் வரும் நோய் அறிகுறிகள் என்ன?🌡🗣 எந்தெந்த காலகட்டத்தில்⏱️⌛எந்த அறிகுறிகள் தென்படலாம். அவற்றை எவ்வாறு வைத்தியம்💉💊🩺 செய்ய வேண்டும் என்று கேட்டு அறிந்து கொள்ளுங்கள்.                                                                          Antibiotic மற்றும் Steriod மருந்துகளை எப்பொழுது உட்கொள்ள வேண்டும். அதன் விளைவுகள் என்னென்ன?                                                                                  Oxygen தேவை மற்றும் செயற்கை சுவாசம் எப்பொழுதெல்லாம் தேவைப்படும் என்பதை இதில் கேட்டு விழிப்புணர்வுடன் இருந்து இந்த நோயினை எதிர்த்து போராடுவோம்.👆🏻

மியூகார் மைகோஸிஸ்🍄 எனப்படும் கருப்பு பூஞ்சை நோய் இப்பொழுது கொரோனா நோய்🦠 வாய்பட்டவர்கள்/நோயில் இருந்து மீண்டவர்கள்  இடையே வேகமாக பரவி வருகிறது. 

சர்க்கரை அளவு கட்டுப்பாட்டில் இல்லாதவர்கள், மருத்துவமனை🏥/ICU-வில் ஆக்சிஜன் சிகிச்சை பெற்றவர்கள், ஸ்டீராய்ட்ஸ்💉 மற்றும் எதிர்ப்பு சக்தி குறைக்கின்ற சிகிச்சை பெறுபவர்களிடையே அதிகமாக கருப்பு பூஞ்சை நோய் காணப்பட்டாலும், தற்போது வீட்டில்🏡 இருந்து சிகிச்சை எடுத்துக் கொண்ட கொரோனா நோயாளிகளிடமும் அதிகரித்து வருகிறது் 

இதைப் பற்றிய விழிப்புணர்விற்கு இந்த வீடியோவை பார்த்து பகிரவும்.

Title: Beware of Black Fungus
Description:
Awareness Regarding Mucormycosis/ Black Fungus Infection

Mucormycosis also known as Black Fungus usually affects people with chronic illness and low immunity. Recently, we are seeing more number of Black Fungus in patients who have recovered from COVID -19.

Who are at risk?

 Managed in ICU/ ventilator for treatment of COVID 19
 Uncontrolled Diabetes Mellitus
 Covered with steroids for COVID -19
 Oxygen support for prolonged duration
 Receiving immunosuppressants for other illness

How dangerous is the infection?

 If left untreated, it can spread through the nose into the brain and can lead to life threatening complications.

 What should you do?

 If you develop any of the above symptoms, immediately seek medical care.
 All patients recovered from COVID -19 must monitor the sugar level everyday and are advised to have good control.
 If blood sugars are uncontrolled, seek medical care immediately.
 People who are using oxygen at home, should ensure sterile water is used for oxygen hydration.
 Avoid self medications and over use of steroids.

Innovation In Ophthalmic Training
Description:
Residency and fellowship training programs are facing huge challenges due to COVID. We implemented various alternative learning strategies by giving importance to safety.  We developed a simulated environment away from the patient's area - Wet lab/ Dry lab training, where all the ophthalmic equipments are placed, so that they could be in touch with the regular ophthalmic skills.

Our video here demonstrates the uses of Wet/Dry lab during covid times for Residents and Fellows to practice ophthalmic skills safely..

Title: eLearning Resources in Ophthalmology - Dr. John Davis Akkara
Giving Life To Surgical Training Through GoPro Live
Description:
Surgical training of residents and fellows in this COVID time has become a real challenge. Surgical video recording with traditional microscope mounted cameras offer a good alternative to teach surgical techniques through the video recordings and reviewing with seniors. However live monitoring  and guiding throughout the surgery is a challenge.

GoPro is a compact action camera mainly used by sportsmen and people involved in extreme action.We have mounted GoPro camera to the side scope of the surgical microscope which is paired with a tablet through GoPro app. This video recording system has turned out to be extremely useful during this COVID times.

Our video demonstrates the various uses of GoPro video recording system and its GO LIVE option in surgical training and live monitoring.

Title: Energy Efficiency for Hospitals by Mr. Arjun Gupta ( Smart Joules)
Description:
Eye Care and Environmental Impact October Summit 2018, Aravind Eye Hospital- Pondicherry 

Hospitals consume high energy by its complex operations and 24*7 functioning. Hospital energy is a major cost factor for hospitals and in turn energy from the Grid cause environmental impact. Title: Leveraging  Green Procurement for Institutions by Mr. Sanjay Kumar (Indian Railways)
Description:
Eye Care and Environmental Impact October Summit 2018, Aravind Eye Hospital- Pondicherry 

Environmentally Preferable Purchasing aims to reduce harm to human health and the environment by integrating environmental considerations into all stages of the purchasing process. Procurement is important to hospitals because they are typically large institutions which consume large quantities of products and services while producing a lot of waste. Hospitals can continually develop their purchase of products and services that are healthier, safer and more environmentally friendly.

Title: Visual Experience During Cataract Surgery
Description:
#cataractsurgery #visualexperience #aravindeyehospital
This video is about visual experience during cataract surgery and different methods to make patient comfortable during cataract surgery

Authors :
Dr. Annamalai Odayappan
Dr. Rengaraj Venkatesh
Dr. Prasanth Gireesh

Aravind Eye Hospital, Pondichery. India

Title: X-NIT Extra-ocular Needle Guided Haptic Insertion Technique for sutureless SF-IOL
Description: This video is about a novel technique to perform sutureless SF-IOL with a MSICS scleral tunnel and it describes a simple technique to externalise the haptic of IOL without doing any intraocular manipulations.

Title: Peri-Screener
Description: This video is about an innovative low cost, portable virtual reality based visual filed testing device called C3FA - C3 stands for Comfortable, Compact and Cost less

Title: Quality Assurance in High Volume Cataract Surgery
Description: This video highlights the quality assurance done at AECS in dealing with high volume cataract surgery

Title: Opportunistic Screening for Glaucoma
Description: This video highlights the different methods followed by AECS for opportunistic screening of glaucoma which is the second leading cause for blindness

Title: Trabeculectomy with MSICS (Tunnel flap method)
Description: This video demonstrates the technique of doing MSICS combined with Trabeculectomy using a tunnel flap technique method.

Title: Novel Glaucoma Screening in an Outreach Eye Camp in a Developing World
Description: This video is about the novel glaucoma screening using low cost high tech equipments including handheld slit-lamp, Rebound tonometer for IOP measurement and Handheld fundus camera for ONH imaging.

Title: Trabeculectomy with MSICS (Triangular scleral flap)
Description: This video demonstrates MSICS combined with Trabeculectomy using a triangular shaped scleral flap.

Title: MSICS in Lens Induced Glaucomas
Description: This ASCRS Film Festival award winning video demonstrates the use of MSICS technique to safely perform cataract surgery in lens induced glaucomas which are very common in underserved population.

Title: Gonio Assisted Transluminal Trabeculotomy in POAG
Description: This video demonstrates the use of suture for doing a low cost and effective gonio assisted transluminal trabeculotomy for POAG patients.

Title: MSICS in different types of cataracts - Aravind way using irrigating vectis
Description: This video demonstrates MSICS in different type of cataracts from simple to couples cases using a irrigating vectis technique.
